{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"shellUnquote","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"quotedString","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">!) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This function only handles quotes; if a string contains file globs,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"arithmetic operators, variables, backticks, redirections, or other","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"special-to-the-shell features, the result will be different from the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"result a real shell would produce (the variables, backticks, etc.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will be passed through literally instead of being expanded).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function is guaranteed to succeed if applied to the result of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_shell_quote()"},{"text":". If it fails, it returns ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" and sets the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"error."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"quotedString"},{"text":" need not actually contain quoted or escaped text;","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_shell_unquote()"},{"text":" simply goes through the string and unquotes\/unescapes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"anything that the shell would. Both single and double quotes are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"handled, as are escapes including escaped newlines.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The return value must be freed with "},{"code":"g_free()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Possible errors are in the "},{"code":"G_SHELL_ERROR","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" domain."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Shell quoting rules are a bit strange. Single quotes preserve the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"literal string exactly. escape sequences are not allowed; not even"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"\\'","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" - if you want a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"'"},{"text":" in the quoted text, you have to do something","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"like "},{"code":"'foo'\\''bar'","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Double quotes allow ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$"},{"text":", ```, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\""},{"text":", ``, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"newline to be escaped with backslash. Otherwise double quotes"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"preserve things literally."}]}]}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Unquotes a string as the shell (\/bin\/sh) would.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"func","title":"shellUnquote(quotedString:)","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Function","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"id